ddi <- read_ipums_ddi("cps_00002.xml")
data <- read_ipums_micro(ddi, verbose = FALSE)
ind_names <- read_csv("~/Desktop/Econometrics/indnames.csv")

# --- 3. Clean and Prepare Data ---
data <- data %>%
  clean_names() %>%
  filter(!is.na(wtfinl), !is.na(empstat), !is.na(uhrsworkt)) %>%
  mutate(across(where(haven::is.labelled), haven::as_factor)) %>%
  mutate(year_month = as.yearmon(paste(year, month), "%Y %B"))

# ========== QUESTION 1: RETAIL EMPLOYMENT & UNEMPLOYMENT ==========

# --- 4. Identify Retail Industries ---
retail_industries <- ind_names %>%
  filter(indname == "Retail Trade") %>%
  pull(ind) %>%
  unique()

retail_data <- data %>%
  filter(ind %in% as.character(retail_industries))

# --- 5. Retail Employment Time Series & Regression ---
retail_employment <- retail_data %>%
  mutate(employed = if_else(empstat %in% c("At work", "Has job, not at work last week"), 1, 0)) %>%
  group_by(year_month) %>%
  summarize(
    total_employed = sum(wtfinl[employed == 1], na.rm = TRUE),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    total_employed_mil = total_employed / 1e6,
    post_covid = if_else(year_month >= as.yearmon("2020-04", "%Y-%m"), 1, 0)
  ) %>%
  arrange(year_month) %>%
  mutate(month_index = row_number())

# Plot: Retail Employment Over Time
ggplot(retail_employment, aes(x = year_month, y = total_employed_mil)) +
  geom_point(color = "darkgreen") +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "steelblue", linewidth = 1) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = as.yearmon("2020-04", "%Y-%m"), linetype = "dashed", color = "black") +
  labs(
    title = "Retail Employment Over Time",
    subtitle = "Dashed line = start of COVID-19 (Apr 2020)",
    x = "Time (Year-Month)", y = "Total Employed (Millions)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

# --- 6. Retail Unemployment Time Series ---
retail_unemployment <- retail_data %>%
  mutate(unemployed = if_else(empstat %in% c("Unemployed", "Unemployed, experienced worker", "Unemployed, new worker"), 1, 0)) %>%
  group_by(year_month) %>%
  summarize(total_unemployed = sum(wtfinl[unemployed == 1], na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop") %>%
  mutate(
    total_unemployed_mil = total_unemployed / 1e6,
    post_covid = if_else(year_month >= as.yearmon("2020-04", "%Y-%m"), 1, 0)
  ) %>%
  arrange(year_month) %>%
  mutate(month_index = row_number())

# Plot: Retail Unemployment Over Time
ggplot(retail_unemployment, aes(x = year_month, y = total_unemployed_mil)) +
  geom_point(color = "darkred") +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "steelblue", linewidth = 1) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = as.yearmon("2020-04", "%Y-%m"), linetype = "dashed", color = "black") +
  labs(
    title = "Retail Unemployment Over Time",
    subtitle = "Dashed line = start of COVID-19 (Apr 2020)",
    x = "Time (Year-Month)", y = "Total Unemployed (Millions)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

# --- 9. Retail Model with Controls (Individual Level) ---
retail_employment_individual <- retail_data %>%
  mutate(
    employed = if_else(empstat %in% c("At work", "Has job, not at work last week"), 1, 0),
    post_covid = if_else(year_month >= as.yearmon("2020-04", "%Y-%m"), 1, 0)
  ) %>%
  select(year_month, month, statefip, age, race, citizen, wtfinl, employed, post_covid)

model_emp_controls <- feols(
  employed ~ post_covid + factor(month) + factor(statefip) + age + factor(race) + factor(citizen),
  weights = ~wtfinl,
  data = retail_employment_individual
)

# ========== QUESTION 2: RETAIL VS NON-RETAIL & INDUSTRY HETEROGENEITY ==========

# --- 10. Retail vs Non-Retail Diff-in-Diff and Plots ---
get_employment_ts <- function(df, label) {
  df %>%
    mutate(employed = if_else(empstat %in% c("At work", "Has job, not at work last week"), 1, 0)) %>%
    group_by(year_month) %>%
    summarize(
      total_employed = sum(wtfinl[employed == 1], na.rm = TRUE),
      .groups = "drop"
    ) %>%
    mutate(
      total_employed_mil = total_employed / 1e6,
      post_covid = if_else(year_month >= as.yearmon("2020-04", "%Y-%m"), 1, 0),
      industry_group = label
    )
}

non_retail_data <- data %>%
  filter(!(ind %in% as.character(retail_industries)))

retail_emp_ts <- get_employment_ts(retail_data, "Retail")
nonretail_emp_ts <- get_employment_ts(non_retail_data, "Non-Retail")
combined_emp_ts <- bind_rows(retail_emp_ts, nonretail_emp_ts) %>%
  arrange(year_month) %>%
  mutate(month_index = row_number(),
         retail = if_else(industry_group == "Retail", 1, 0),
         interaction = post_covid * retail)

# Plot: Retail vs Non-Retail Employment Trends
ggplot(combined_emp_ts, aes(x = year_month, y = total_employed_mil, color = industry_group)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, linewidth = 1.2) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = as.yearmon("2020-04"), linetype = "dashed", color = "black") +
  labs(
    title = "Employment Trends: Retail vs. Non-Retail",
    subtitle = "Dashed line = start of COVID-19 (April 2020)",
    x = "Time (Year-Month)", y = "Total Employed (Millions)", color = "Industry Group"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

# Regression: Retail vs Non-Retail (Diff-in-Diff)
model_diff <- feols(
  total_employed_mil ~ post_covid + retail + interaction + month_index,
  data = combined_emp_ts
)
etable(model_diff, tex = FALSE)

# --- 11. Retail vs. Non-Retail: Average Employment Rate Analysis ---
labor_data <- data %>%
  filter(empstat %in% c("At work", "Has job, not at work last week",
                        "Unemployed", "Unemployed, experienced worker", 
                        "Unemployed, new worker")) %>%
  mutate(
    employed = if_else(empstat %in% c("At work", "Has job, not at work last week"), 1, 0),
    year_month = as.yearmon(paste(year, month), "%Y %B"),
    post_covid = if_else(year_month >= as.yearmon("2020-04"), 1, 0),
    retail = if_else(ind %in% retail_industries, 1, 0)
  )

industry_monthly <- labor_data %>%
  group_by(ind, year_month) %>%
  summarize(
    avg_employed = weighted.mean(employed, wtfinl, na.rm = TRUE),
    post_covid = first(post_covid),
    retail = first(retail),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) %>%
  arrange(year_month) %>%
  mutate(month_index = as.numeric(as.factor(year_month)))

model_avg_diff <- feols(
  avg_employed ~ post_covid * retail + month_index | ind + year_month,
  data = industry_monthly
)
## The variables 'post_covid', 'retail' and 'month_index' have been removed because of collinearity (see $collin.var).
etable(model_avg_diff, tex = FALSE)

# --- 12. Heterogeneity: Compare Retail with All Major Industry Groups ---
# Identify industry groups for heterogeneity
manufacturing_inds <- ind_names %>% filter(str_detect(indname, "Manufacturing")) %>% pull(ind) %>% unique()
services_inds <- ind_names %>% filter(str_detect(indname, "Services|Finance|Health|Education")) %>% pull(ind) %>% unique()
hospitality_inds <- ind_names %>% filter(str_detect(indname, "Accommodation|Food Services")) %>% pull(ind) %>% unique()

data <- data %>%
  mutate(
    industry_group = case_when(
      ind %in% retail_industries ~ "Retail",
      ind %in% manufacturing_inds ~ "Manufacturing",
      ind %in% services_inds ~ "Services",
      ind %in% hospitality_inds ~ "Hospitality",
      TRUE ~ "Other"
    )
  )

data <- data %>%
  mutate(employed = if_else(empstat %in% c("At work", "Has job, not at work last week"), 1, 0))

industry_group_ts <- data %>%
  group_by(year_month, industry_group) %>%
  summarize(
    total_employed = sum(wtfinl[employed == 1], na.rm = TRUE),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    total_employed_mil = total_employed / 1e6,
    post_covid = if_else(year_month >= as.yearmon("2020-04", "%Y-%m"), 1, 0)
  ) %>%
  arrange(year_month) %>%
  mutate(month_index = row_number())


industry_group_ts$industry_group <- factor(
  industry_group_ts$industry_group,
  levels = c("Retail", "Manufacturing", "Services", "Hospitality", "Other")
)

# Plot: Employment Trends by Industry Group
ggplot(industry_group_ts, aes(x = year_month, y = total_employed_mil, color = industry_group)) +
  geom_line(linewidth = 1.1) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = as.yearmon("2020-04"), linetype = "dashed", color = "black") +
  labs(
    title = "Employment Trends by Industry Group",
    subtitle = "Comparison of Retail and Non-Retail Sectors",
    x = "Year-Month", y = "Total Employed (Millions)", color = "Industry Group"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

# Regression: post_covid interacted with industry group (Retail as reference)
model_het <- feols(
  total_employed_mil ~ post_covid * industry_group + month_index,
  data = industry_group_ts
)

# ========== QUESTION 3: EARNINGS REGRESSIONS (NO DUPLICATES WITH Q1 & Q2) ==========

# --- A. Difference-in-Differences Regression (Group Means, Q3-specific names) ---
# Reload and clean data for Q3 earnings analysis
ddi_q3 <- read_ipums_ddi("~/Desktop/Econometrics/cps_00002.xml")
data_q3 <- read_ipums_micro(ddi_q3)
## Use of data from IPUMS CPS is subject to conditions including that users should cite the data appropriately. Use command `ipums_conditions()` for more details.
retail_codes_df_q3 <- read_csv("indnames.csv")
## Rows: 8185 Columns: 2
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (1): indname
## dbl (1): ind
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
# Confirm correct column name for industry code if needed
colnames(retail_codes_df_q3)
## [1] "indname" "ind"
retail_industry_codes_q3 <- unique(retail_codes_df_q3$code) # change "code" if needed
## Warning: Unknown or uninitialised column: `code`.
employed_labels_q3 <- c("At work", "Has job, not at work last week")
data_q3 <- data_q3 %>%
  clean_names() %>%
  mutate(across(where(haven::is.labelled), haven::as_factor))

valid_hours_q3 <- as.character(0:200)
cleaned_data_q3 <- data_q3 %>%
  filter(!is.na(year), !is.na(month)) %>%
  mutate(
    month_chr_q3 = as.character(month),
    month_num_q3 = match(month_chr_q3, month.name)
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(month_num_q3)) %>%
  filter(empstat %in% employed_labels_q3) %>%
  filter(!(uhrsworkt %in% c("NIU", "Hours vary"))) %>%
  mutate(
    employed_q3 = 1,
    post_covid_q3 = if_else(year > 2020 | (year == 2020 & month_num_q3 >= 4), 1, 0),
    is_retail_q3 = ind %in% retail_industry_codes_q3,
    uhrs_numeric_q3 = as.numeric(as.character(uhrsworkt)),
    earnings_q3 = if_else(uhrs_numeric_q3 > 0, uhrs_numeric_q3 * 15, NA_real_),
    weight_q3 = if_else(is.na(wtfinl) | wtfinl == 0, NA_real_, wtfinl)
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(weight_q3), !is.na(earnings_q3), uhrs_numeric_q3 %in% valid_hours_q3)

employment_summary_q3 <- cleaned_data_q3 %>%
  group_by(year, month, is_retail_q3, post_covid_q3) %>%
  summarise(
    avg_earnings_q3 = mean(earnings_q3, na.rm = TRUE),
    n_q3 = n(),
    .groups = "drop"
  )

employment_summary_filtered_q3 <- employment_summary_q3 %>%
  filter(!(year == 2022 & month != "April")) %>%
  mutate(
    year = factor(year),
    month = factor(month)
  )

model_did_q3 <- lm(
  avg_earnings_q3 ~ is_retail_q3 * post_covid_q3 + year + month,
  data = employment_summary_filtered_q3
)
summary(model_did_q3)

# --- B. Demographic Earnings Regression (Individual Level, Q3-specific names) ---
cleaned_data_demog_q3 <- cleaned_data_q3 %>%
  mutate(
    age_q3 = as.numeric(as.character(age)),
    race_group_q3 = case_when(
      race == "White" ~ "White",
      race == "Black" ~ "Black",
      str_detect(race, "Asian") ~ "Asian",
      TRUE ~ "Other"
    ),
    race_group_q3 = factor(race_group_q3),
    age_group_q3 = case_when(
      age_q3 < 25 ~ "Under 25",
      age_q3 >= 25 & age_q3 < 45 ~ "25–44",
      age_q3 >= 45 & age_q3 < 65 ~ "45–64",
      age_q3 >= 65 ~ "65+"
    ),
    age_group_q3 = factor(age_group_q3)
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(race_group_q3), !is.na(age_group_q3)) %>%
  droplevels()

model_demog_q3 <- lm(
  earnings_q3 ~ post_covid_q3 * age_group_q3 + post_covid_q3 * race_group_q3,
  data = cleaned_data_demog_q3,
  weights = weight_q3
)
summary(model_demog_q3)
